AS INTRODUCED
6
7
An Act relating to state fiscal affairs; requiring
7
entities of this state and certain entities to round
8
the price of certain transactions paid with cash;
8
prescribing procedure for rounding; providing for
9
codification; providing an effective date; and
9
declaring an emergency.
10
10
11
11
12
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12
13
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3120 of Title 74, unless there
14
15
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
For any agency, constitutionally or statutorily created state
16
17
board, bureau, commission, office, authority, public trust in which
17
18
the state is a beneficiary, or interstate commission accepting cash
18
19
as payment from an individual, such entity shall adjust the price,
19
20
fee, penalty, or any other charge, excluding the payment of any tax
20
21
levy, by rounding the total amount of the transaction down to the
21
22
nearest cent that is a multiple of five. Provided, if the
22
23
individual making payment is using both cash and another form of
23
24
24
